<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>PS00076</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : STRESSED THE NEED TO STRENGTHEN VOLUNTARY ACCREDITATION AMONG HIGHER EDUCATION INSTITUTIONS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Voluntary Accreditation System; Quality Of The Country's Higher Education</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : . . . Rep. Olivarez stressed the need to strengthen voluntary accreditation among higher education institutions (HEIs) in order for the country to cope with global competitiveness.
He cited facts and figures on the number of HEIs in the country and their student population, the low passing rate in licensure examinations,the small percentage of masterâ€™s degree-holders among college faculty, and the warning among the business community on the economic impact of inadequately trained and prepared graduates...; also discussed Memo Order No. 1 (2005) of the CHED on the policies and guidelines on accreditation and described what was being
done about accreditation in the context of the ASEAN community...; stated that he would file a measure to strengthen voluntary accreditation in the Philippines by institutionalizing its existing policies and practices and providing financial assistance therefor. 
(SOURCE: House Journal No.23,p.15)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>OLIVAREZ, ERIC L.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-09-19</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Speech-Privilege Hour</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HIGHER AND TECHNICAL EDUCATION ON 2016-10-12</td></tr></table>